SUSPENSE STRING

Alice and Bob are playing a game using a binary string S of length N and an initially empty string T.

They take turns alternately, with Alice playing first.

RULES

Alice’s turn
She picks the first character of string S
She can insert it either at the front or at the back of string T
Then she removes that character from S

Bob’s turn
He picks the last character of string S
He can insert it either at the front or at the back of string T
Then he removes that character from S

The game continues until S becomes empty.

OBJECTIVE

Alice wants the final string T to be lexicographically smallest
Bob wants the final string T to be lexicographically largest

Both players play optimally.

TASK

Find the final string T after the game ends.

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer T
T is the number of test cases

For each test case
The first line contains an integer N
The second line contains the binary string S

OUTPUT FORMAT

For each test case, print the final string T

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ T ≤ 100
1 ≤ N ≤ 1000
S contains only characters 0 and 1

SAMPLE INPUT

4
2
10
4
0001
6
010111
10
1110000010

SAMPLE OUTPUT

10
0100
101101
0011011000

EXPLANATION

Players alternately pick characters from S and place them at either end of T.
Alice tries to minimize the final string, while Bob tries to maximize it.
The final result depends on optimal decisions made by both players.
======================================
import java.util.*;
public class Main{
    public static void main (String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int t=sc.nextInt();
        while(t-->0){
            int n=sc.nextInt();
            sc.nextLine();
            String s=sc.nextLine();
            Deque <Character> r=new ArrayDeque<>();
            int i=0,j=n-1;
            boolean alice=true;
            while(i<=j){
                char ch=s.charAt(i);
                if(alice) {
                    ch=s.charAt(i++);
                    if(ch=='0'){
                        r.addFirst(ch);
                    } else{
                        r.addLast(ch);
                    } } 
                    else{
                    ch=s.charAt(j--);
                    if(ch=='1'){
                        r.addFirst(ch);
                    }else{
                        r.addLast(ch);
                    } }
               alice=!alice;}
            while(!r.isEmpty()){
                System.out.print(r.pollFirst());
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}


